\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0 At Unug, the great goddess was celebrated under the name Inanna. But here it was her harlotry, her aspect as whore, that was most emphasized. Cities were always, until modern times, greater consumers rather than producers of humanity. The people who thronged the narrow lanes between high walls, cheek by jowl with the poultry and livestock from which most human epidemics spread, did not live long. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8216\'91One-third of all babies perished before their first birthday; half of all children died before five; on third of population under 15. Fewer than 10 per cent were over 55. }
